The paper deals with image processing and regularization techniques for inverse problems, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The use of patch-based methods and wavelet pyramids also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the optimization techniques used in the paper may also relate to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
